## 3. Data Flow — Linking a FleetEdge Account

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant FE as FleetEdge Tab
    participant Spy as networkSpy.js<br/>(MAIN world)
    participant Reader as fleetedgeTokenReader.js<br/>(ISOLATED world)
    participant SW as Service Worker<br/>(fleetedgeLink.js)
    participant BE as GNB Backend<br/>(/api/extension)
    participant DB as MongoDB

    User->>FE: Logs into FleetEdge
    Note over Spy: Monkey-patches XHR & fetch<br/>on page load (document_start)
    FE->>Spy: Any request with Auth: Bearer …
    Spy->>Reader: postMessage({token, fleetId, type:'FLEETEDGE_INTERCEPT'})

    User->>SW: Clicks "Connect FleetEdge"
    SW->>SW: Check permissions for fleetedge host
    SW->>FE: chrome.tabs.query({url: fleetedge...})
    SW->>Reader: chrome.tabs.sendMessage(tab.id, {type:'READ_FLEETEDGE_TOKEN'})
    Reader->>Reader: Return intercepted token (preferred)<br/>OR scan localStorage fallback
    Reader-->>SW: {success, token, fleetId, exp, foundIn}

    alt Token expires < 10 min
        SW-->>User: Error: "Token expires in X min — refresh FleetEdge"
    else Token valid
        SW->>BE: POST /fleetedge/link-token<br/>{token, fleetId}
        BE->>BE: Validate token against FleetEdge CVP
        BE->>DB: Upsert UserFleetEdgeToken<br/>(encrypted, expiresAt, ACTIVE)
        BE-->>SW: {accountId, vehicleCount, expiresAt}
        SW->>BE: GET /fleetedge/status (refresh accounts)
        BE-->>SW: {accounts, pull}
        SW->>SW: chrome.storage.local.set({fleetEdgeAccounts})<br/>updateBadge('✓' green)
        SW-->>User: Popup shows new account card
    end
```

